title: For Sale:  1940 Winchester Model 62 .22 Pre-war Takedown
postcontent: This is a very nice looking example of a Winchester Model 62 rifle in .22LR. dates production to 1940. The blued finish of the receiver rates at approximately 94% with finish on underside of the trigger guard, lower tang and receiver beginning to turn slight patina. The bluing on the barrel and magazine tube show only the slightest occasional freckling too small to photo. The top of the barrel behind the rear sight shows some light, shallow dings for some unknown reason. The walnut stock and fore end show intermittent handling marks. While the stock and fore end have never been sanded, I believe that a very light coating of varnish or tru-oil was applied at some time. The action is smooth and tight, and the bore is very shiny and crisp! If the wood did not have the light varnish, we would rate it at over 95%, but alas, we cannot. This is an excellent rifle for someone to carefully clean up and bring back to original and the price is right!
